    "blurb_en": "Founded in 1848 by Louis Brandt in La Chaux-de-Fonds and now headquartered in Biel/Bienne, Omega is among Switzerland's most celebrated watchmakers, known for its co-axial escapement and highly anti-magnetic Master Chronometer movements. The brand is tied to landmark moments in timekeeping, from NASA's Moon missions to its long role as official Olympic timekeeper. Its Seamaster, Speedmaster, and Constellation lines rank among the most recognized in watchmaking.",
